## 📌 Project Overview

This project analyzes **e-commerce consumer behavior in the Philippines** using:
- Transactional customer data
- Google Trends data
- Consumer survey responses

It applies **data analytics and machine learning techniques** to extract insights and presents results through an **interactive R Shiny dashboard**.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

- Predict customer spending behavior
- Segment customers into value-based groups
- Identify best-selling product categories
- Analyze consumer interest trends over time
- Support data-driven business decisions

---

## 📊 Key Features

- Data cleaning and preprocessing (ETL pipeline)
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Multiple Linear Regression (Spending Prediction)
- K-Means Clustering (Customer Segmentation)
- Interactive dashboards using Shiny
- Visualization using ggplot2 & Plotly

---

## 🧠 Machine Learning Models

### 📈 Multiple Linear Regression
Used to predict total customer spending based on:
- Age
- Items Purchased
- Average Rating
- Days Since Last Purchase

### 👥 K-Means Clustering
Segments customers into:
- High-Value Customers
- Medium-Value Customers
- Low-Value Customers

---

